        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> First of all, the EoT was NOT FOCUSED.  It was hitting for 69 instead of 73.  Thats probably good, if the EoT won, the nerf parade would have started. </P><P> Also, I could put a damage shield on a tree stump and it would beat a pet.  Whats the point of damage shielding a pet in pet to pet duels?  DS is a SPELL YOU CAST.  Do we cast any spells on our pets besides the obvious haste?  I know the epic has an inate DS, but why bother dueling if a DS is involved? </P><P> EoT would have to do 3500 damage or whatever the Epic pet has for hps.  Now say it averages 35 a hit, it needs to hit the epic 100 times to kill it.  With a 33 point DS, that is 3300 damage to the EoT, WAY more hps then it has.  So you could just hit /pet back off and the epic would still win if it had a DS on it.  Its a stupid comparison of pet power.  The DS does all the work and the pets real offense/defense skills mean little.</P><P> </font></td>
